# Code Generator (Codegen) in Playwright
1️⃣ What is Codegen?
Codegen (Code generator) in Playwright is a tool that automatically generates automation test scripts by recording user actions on the browser.

When you interact with a website (click , type , navigate) , Playwright records those actions and converts them into playwright code.

👉 Simple definition:
    Codegen = Tool that records browser actions and generates playwright automation code automatically.

2️⃣ Why Codegen is Useful
Codegen helps tests and developers to:
    1. Quicly generates automation scripts
    2. Identify reliable locators
    3. Learn playwright syntax
    4. Save development time
It is expecially helpful for beginners learning playwright.

3️⃣ Command to Start Codegen
Basic command:
    playwright codegen

Example:
    playwright codegen https://example.com

This will:
    1. Open a browser
    2. Open playwright inspector
    3. Start recording user actions

4️⃣ Codegen Interface
When codegen starts , two windows open:
    1️⃣ Browser Window
    Used to interact with the application
    Example:
        1. click buttons
        2. Enter text
        3. Navigate pages
        4. Select options
    
    2️⃣ Playwright Inspector
    Displays generated playwright code in real-time
    Example output:
        page.goto("https://example.com")
        page.get_by_label("Username").fill("admin")
        page.get_by_label("Password").fill("admin123")
        page.get_by_role("button", name="Login").click()
    
5️⃣ Example Workflow
Step-by-Step example:
    Command:
        playwright codegen https://example.com
    
Actions Performed:
    1. Enter username
    2. Enter password
    3. Click login

Generated code:
    page.goto("https://example.com")
    page.get_by_label("Username").fill("admin")
    page.get_by_label("Password").fill("admin123")
    page.get_by_role("button", name="Login").click()

6️⃣ Locator Generation
One of the best features of Codegen is automatic locator generation.
Playwright automatically suggests best locator strategies such as:
    1. get_by_role()
    2. get_by_text()
    3. get_by_label()
    4. get_by_placeholder()

Example generated locator:
    page.get_by_role("button" , name = "login")
This helps create stable automation scripts.

7️⃣ Codegen Locator Picker
The locator picker allows selecting elements directly.
Steps:
    1. Click pick locator in inspector
    2. Click element in browser
    3. Playwright generates the locator

Example generated locator:
    page.get_by_text("Submit")

8️⃣ Recording Actions
Codegen records various user actions.
Examples:
    Action & Generate code
    ----------------------
    1. Click -> page.click()
    2. Fill input -> page.fill()
    3. select dropdown -> page.select_option()
    4. check checkbox -> page.check()
    5. Navigate page -> page.goto()

Example:
    page.get_by_label("Email").fill("user@test.com")

9️⃣ Saving Generated Code
The generated code can be copied and pasted into test scripts.
Example test file:
    test_login.py

Example usage:
    def test_login(page):

    page.goto("https://example.com")

    page.get_by_label("Username").fill("admin")
    page.get_by_label("Password").fill("admin123")

    page.get_by_role("button", name="Login").click()

🔟 Codegen with Different Browsers
Codegen supports multiple browsers.
Example:
    playwright codegen --browser chromium

Other options:
    playwright codegen --browser firefox
    playwright codegen --browser webkit

1️⃣1️⃣ Codegen with Device Emulation
Playwright supports mobile device recording.
Example:
    playwright codegen --device="iPhone 13"

this opens browser with mobile viewport and user agent.
Useful for mobile automation testing.

1️⃣2️⃣ Codegen with Authentication
You can start Codegen on a logged-in a page.
Example:
    playwright codegen https://example.com/dashboard
then record actions on authenticated pages.

1️⃣3️⃣ Codegen for Learning Playwright
Codegen is very helpful when:
    1. Learning playwright syntax
    2. Finding element locators
    3. Understanding automation flow.

Example:
    You click an element -> Codegen shows the exact playwright command.

1️⃣4️⃣ Limitations of Codegen
Although useful , Codegen should not be used to generate full frameworks.
Problems:
    1. Generate code may not follow best practice
    2. Code may need refactoring
    3. Not optimised for large test suites

Best approach:
    Use Codegen for reference only.

1️⃣5️⃣ Best Practices When Using Codegen
1. Use Codegen to find locators
2. Clean up generated code
3. Add assertions manually
4. Convert recorded steps into reusable functions

